id: pm-gt82
title: Bundle CLI with esbuild for sub-200ms startup
description: Startup is 890ms+ for simple commands; bundling reduces this to ~100ms
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 0
tags[2]: performance,startup
created_at: "2026-05-16T15:07:08.622Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-23T11:25:23.523Z"
author: claude-code-agent
comments[25]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-16T16:48:23.232Z",codex-agent,"Audit update 2026-05-16: latest isolated dogfood after init --with-packages passed 44 workflows; slowest normal commands were create 753ms, comments 683ms, package wildcard 634ms, notes/docs/learnings/get brief around 560-600ms. Release gate is green, but sub-200ms startup remains the largest remaining perceived-speed opportunity."
  "2026-05-16T16:59:45.913Z",codex-audit,"Implementation update: adding a build-time bundled dist/cli.js path for the pm binary while keeping SDK/module exports emitted by tsc. Package-root resolution is being made independent of unbundled dist/cli/** module paths so package discovery, guide docs, upgrade version reads, telemetry flush, and Sentry release tagging continue to work from the bundled entrypoint."
  "2026-05-16T17:07:21.271Z",codex-audit,"Benchmark finding: attempted esbuild bundling first, but the safe dependency-external ESM bundle averaged 234.9ms for node dist/cli.js --version versus 201.7ms for the tsc entry, so it was not shipped. Implemented a targeted fast --version/-V path instead; after build, node dist/cli.js --version averages 36.7ms versus 194.6ms for loading dist/cli/main.js, a 5.3x speedup for the standard agent bootstrap probe. Remaining all-command sub-200ms bundling stays open for a deeper CJS/import-meta redesign."
  "2026-05-16T17:13:35.708Z",codex-audit,"Evidence: shipped targeted startup win and kept broader bundling scope honest. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts (31 tests), pm test pm-gt82 --run sandboxed schema context, node scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs (44 workflows), pnpm quality:static, node scripts/check-secrets.mjs, pm health --refresh-vectors (refreshed pm-p7av; zero stale vectors), hybrid search probe, and full release gate with required Sentry/telemetry. Remaining open scope: all-command sub-200ms startup still needs deeper command graph lazy-loading or a CJS-compatible bundle design."
  "2026-05-16T20:47:15.091Z",codex-agent,"Performance evidence 2026-05-16: current isolated dogfood passed 44 workflows. Slowest normal commands in the post-doc-fix run were init 1032ms, config 745ms, create 646ms, update 614ms, files 571ms, claim 567ms, health 530ms; linked test execution 6767ms. No startup implementation change in this pass; broader sub-200ms all-command startup remains open."
  "2026-05-17T09:11:07.381Z",codex-agent,"Kickoff 2026-05-17: startup-only optimization pass under pm-rnpb lineage. Next steps are before/after latency baselines for --version/help/list/get/contracts, safe bootstrap-path optimization, contract parity checks, dogfood in isolated PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH sandbox, and full release-gate verification."
  "2026-05-17T09:12:10.950Z",codex-agent,"Baseline profiling 2026-05-17 before code edits (6-run cold+warm): --version cold=38ms warm_avg=36.8ms; --help cold=198ms warm_avg=190ms; list --json --limit 1 cold=383ms warm_avg=408.2ms; get pm-rnpb --depth brief cold=330ms warm_avg=326.2ms; contracts --flags-only cold=327ms warm_avg=349.4ms. Extension-overhead 8-run comparison: list default avg=469.8ms vs --no-extensions avg=409.4ms (~60ms delta); contracts default avg=332.9ms vs --no-extensions avg=316.9ms (~16ms delta). --profile traces captured for list/get/contracts to isolate extension/runtime-schema behavior."
  "2026-05-17T09:14:57.712Z",codex-agent,"Implementation update 2026-05-17: optimized bootstrap path in src/cli/main.ts by lazily loading command-family registration modules (setup/list-query/mutation/operation) based on the invocation command, and attaching rich help narratives only for bare/help invocations. This avoids unnecessary registration/help payload work on normal execution paths while preserving full registration for help and unknown-command flows."
  "2026-05-17T09:17:39.943Z",codex-agent,"Token/contract parity verification 2026-05-17: startup bootstrap changes did not alter list/search/help contract surfaces. Confirmed contracts --command list-open --flags-only still exposes --compact/--brief/--full/--fields/--include-body, contracts --command search --flags-only still exposes --mode/--semantic/--hybrid/--include-linked, and top-level plus list help still render rich Intent narratives on help paths."
  "2026-05-17T09:27:50.721Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence 2026-05-17 startup pass: after lazy command-family registration + help-attach gating in src/cli/main.ts, post-change 8-run warm medians improved on key commands versus pre-change baseline (help 183.6ms vs 190ms, list --json --limit 1 382.1ms vs 408.2ms, get --depth brief 311.3ms vs 326.2ms, contracts --flags-only 309.6ms vs 349.4ms). Isolated dogfood passed in temp sandboxes for both default (51 commands) and semantic mode (52 commands, qwen3-embedding:0.6b). Full release gate passed with telemetry+sentry required: build/typecheck/docs/static quality/coverage/version policy/secrets/npx/npm-pack/compatibility all ok; tests 1323/1323 with 100% coverage; sentry critical/high/total 0; telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 2.13 with missing-error-code rows 0."
  "2026-05-17T09:28:29.427Z",codex-agent,"Privacy/observability verification 2026-05-17: node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed; targeted rg sweeps over .agents/pm for credential tokens/private-key blocks/private IPv4/home-path/user@host patterns found no active secret material. Direct sentry-telemetry gate passed in required mode (sentry critical/high/total=0/0/0, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.13, failures_without_error_code_rows=0)."
  "2026-05-22T16:21:07.143Z",codex-review-followup,"Review follow-up: PR #41 has unresolved CodeRabbit/Gemini threads on vNumber finite/safe-integer parity. Outside-diff .agents/pm warnings are bot false positives for this repo because tracker mutations must go through pm CLI and generate .agents/pm artifacts; no direct manual file edits will be made."
  "2026-05-22T16:29:54.345Z",codex-review-followup,"Evidence: addressed PR #41 reviewer finite-number feedback. Local verification passed: pnpm build; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/settings-validator.spec.ts (19 tests); pnpm quality:static; pm test pm-gt82 --run --progress (6/6 linked tests passed, including release gate 1433/1433 tests with 100% coverage, dogfood 84 workflows, semantic dogfood 86 workflows, sentry critical/high/total 0/0/0, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct 3.24). Secret scan passed after pm evidence updates."
  "2026-05-23T10:43:53.854Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Execution start 2026-05-23: duplicate/orientation commands reused existing priority-0 startup feature pm-gt82 under in-progress parent pm-rnpb; no duplicate item created. Bootstrap passed: npm install -g ., pm --version 2026.5.23, node v25.9.0, pnpm 10.33.0, pnpm build. Runtime-contract correction: pm get is the current detail command, and pm deps uses --format tree rather than --tree. Proceeding with specialized sub-agent lanes for startup profiling, store/index cost, and observability validation; all findings will be recorded back to this item."
  "2026-05-23T10:45:54.735Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Implementation update 2026-05-23: added guarded Node compile-cache bootstrap in src/cli.ts for normal commands while preserving the existing fast --version path and lazy Sentry startup. Cache can be disabled with PM_CLI_DISABLE_COMPILE_CACHE=1 or redirected with PM_CLI_COMPILE_CACHE_DIR. Local before/after probe on current checkout: list --json --limit 1 warm avg improved from ~404ms to ~312ms; contracts --command list --flags-only --json from ~414ms to ~245ms; get pm-gt82 --depth brief from ~249ms to ~220ms; --version remains ~32-35ms because it stays on the fast path."
  "2026-05-23T10:46:16.097Z",codex-observability-startup-2026-05-23,"Observability/privacy evidence 2026-05-23T10:45Z: tracked secret scan passed (no credential-like secrets in tracked files); pm health --check-only --brief --json ok=true with telemetry enabled/redacted, local queue_entries=5, queue_draining=true, queue_invalid_rows=0, last_successful_flush_at=2026-05-23T10:45:17Z, no warnings; release Sentry/telemetry gate passed in required mode with Sentry checked via token-backed CLI/API path, critical=0, high=0, total=0, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=3.05, missing_error_code_rows=0; live telemetry stack healthy with API ok, worker up, RabbitMQ pm.telemetry.events drained (0 ready/0 total) with 1 consumer, and 5118 events in the last 24h; direct Sentry unresolved snapshots for 24h and 7d returned 0 issues. Privacy finding: no new tracked-secret leak found; keep existing history-stream redaction work under pm-xk39 separate from this release gate."
  "2026-05-23T10:47:24.499Z",codex-store-index-specialist-2026-05-23,"Store/index cost specialist evidence 2026-05-23:\nScope: read-only source investigation plus timing probes; no source edits. Bootstrap verified with npm install -g ., pm --version => 2026.5.23, node -v => v25.9.0, pnpm -v => 10.33.0, pnpm build => pass.\nCommands/probes: pm context/search/list-in-progress confirmed reuse of pm-gt82; inspected src/core/store/item-store.ts, src/core/store/front-matter-cache.ts, src/cli/commands/list.ts, search.ts, context.ts, get.ts, tests/unit/front-matter-cache.spec.ts, item-store.spec.ts, list-command.spec.ts, context-command.spec.ts. Runtime artifact check: .agents/pm/runtime/metadata-cache.json is ~4.5MB with 829 cached entries and cached bodies; search/vectorization-status.json and local lancedb exist, but .agents/pm/index/manifest.json is absent.\nTiming on warmed checkout with telemetry/sentry disabled: shell pm list-open --limit 5 --json ~0.34-0.54s; pm context --limit 5 --json ~0.44-0.70s; pm search startup --limit 5 --json ~0.56s; pm get pm-gt82 --fields id,title,status,updated_at --json ~0.41s first shell probe, ~0.22s later. In-process dist probes isolate store cost: listAllFrontMatter warm ~142-156ms for 829 entries; runList open limit5 ~224ms; runSearch startup limit5 ~172ms; runContext brief limit5 ~237ms; runGet existing fields ~7-17ms, default get ~39ms; missing get did-you-mean path ~141ms.\nFindings: list/search/context are scan-bound because front-matter-cache still readdir's all type folders, stats every item file, runs onRead hooks for every file, reconstructs/sorts all candidates, and persists a full cache envelope on every read before command-level filters/limits apply. list applies limit only after full load/filter/sort. context calls runList once and for standard/deep can call runList a second time, compounding the same scan. keyword search also loads all cached documents and scores all filtered documents; the cache avoids parsing unchanged files but is not an index for status/type/tag/parent/updated_at/title/body tokens. get for an existing id is not item-scan-bound in core; it uses locateItem path probes plus one item read and optional history read. get missing-id suggestions still scan known ids.\nRecommended low-risk implementation: add a store-owned runtime index layer in src/core/store/front-matter-cache.ts or a new src/core/store/item-index.ts that persists sorted rows keyed by id and path, includes secondary maps for status/type/tags/parent/assignee/deadline/updated_at plus a lightweight token index for title/description/body/comments/notes/learnings, and exposes query helpers used by list/search/context before falling back to current listAll* functions. Keep the existing cache parser as the rebuild source; add a stale check using directory entry count plus per-path mtime/ctime/size, and only rewrite the cache/index when entries changed. Preserve runActiveOnReadHooks semantics by firing hooks only for returned/read rows by default, with a compatibility/full-scan fallback for extension modes that require per-file reads. For get, optionally add an id->LocatedItem lookup from the same index and keep locateItem as fallback; optimize not-found suggestions from the id set.\nFiles/functions to edit next: src/core/store/front-matter-cache.ts:listAllDocumentCandidatesCached; src/core/store/item-store.ts:locateItem/listAllFrontMatter/listAllFrontMatterWithBody/listKnownItemIds; src/cli/commands/list.ts:runList; src/cli/commands/search.ts:loadDocuments/runSearch keyword path; src/cli/commands/context.ts:runContext; src/cli/commands/get.ts:runGet not-found path. Tests to extend: tests/unit/front-matter-cache.spec.ts, item-store.spec.ts, list-command.spec.ts, search-command.spec.ts, context-command.spec.ts, get-append-command.spec.ts. Main risks: extension onRead hook compatibility, stale cache/index after out-of-band file mutation, custom item type folder/format preference handling, and memory/cache growth from indexing full bodies.\n"
  "2026-05-23T10:47:29.899Z",codex-startup-profiler-2026-05-23,"Startup profiling evidence 2026-05-23 by codex-startup-profiler-2026-05-23. Bootstrap: npm install -g . (already up to date), pm --version=2026.5.23, node -v=v25.9.0, pnpm -v=10.33.0, pnpm build passed. Duplicate check/orient: pm context --limit 10, pm search \"startup profiling performance pm-gt82\" --limit 10, pm list-open --limit 20, pm list-in-progress --limit 20; reused active pm-gt82, no new item created. Built-in --profile commands inspected: pm --profile --version and pm --profile --no-extensions --version print only 2026.5.23 because the fast path bypasses main/profile; pm --profile --help and --no-extensions --help print help only; pm --profile list --json --limit 1 => profile:extensions loaded=1 command_handlers=1, profile:command=list took_ms=351; pm --profile --no-extensions list --json --limit 1 => took_ms=334; pm --profile get pm-gt82 --depth brief => extensions loaded=1, get took_ms=174; no-extensions get => 173; pm --profile context --limit 3 => extensions loaded=1, context took_ms=490; no-extensions context => 485; pm --profile contracts --command list --flags-only --json => extensions loaded=1, contracts took_ms=170; no-extensions contracts => 214. Wall-clock hyperfine command: hyperfine --warmup 1 --runs 5 --export-json /tmp/pm-startup-hyperfine-20260523.json [12 requested command variants]. Medians: --version 43.5ms; --no-extensions --version 102.1ms (slower because --no-extensions misses the single-arg fast path); --help 146.5ms; --no-extensions --help 108.2ms; list --json --limit 1 385.9ms; no-extensions list 334.6ms; get pm-gt82 --depth brief 249.0ms; no-extensions get 243.3ms; context --limit 3 599.7ms; no-extensions context 536.9ms; contracts --command list --flags-only --json 251.5ms; no-extensions contracts 230.1ms. CPU/import-load spot check command: node --cpu-prof --cpu-prof-dir=/tmp/pm-startup-cpu-20260523 --cpu-prof-name={list,context,contracts}.cpuprofile dist/cli.js ... . Hot spots: list total_samples=270 with front-matter-cache.js 40 samples/14.8% (loadCache 5.9%, persistCache 5.6%), package_json_reader 5.9%, settings.js 4.4%, cli-contracts.js/main.js each 3.0%; context total_samples=359 with front-matter-cache.js 68/18.9% (loadCache 8.1%, persistCache 8.1%), buffer/path/fs-promises/string_decoder load/write cost, settings.js 3.6%; contracts total_samples=186 with package_json_reader 9.1%, settings.js 8.1%, esm loader/utils/cjs loader ~18.8% combined, cli-contracts.js 3.8%, main.js 2.7%. Findings: extension loading in this checkout is only one handler and usually costs about 5-60ms; it is not the main remaining blocker. Remaining startup cost is dominated by importing full cli/main for non-version commands, settings/package-json/ESM loader work, and list/context repeatedly loading and persisting metadata-cache even on read-only cache-hit paths.\n"
  "2026-05-23T10:47:36.446Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Manual temp-project evidence 2026-05-23: PASS in /tmp/pm-cli-startup-smoke-TJC1CP using repo dist/cli.js with isolated PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH. Covered init --defaults --with-packages, create/claim/update, linked files/docs/comments/notes/learnings, linked test run --progress, plan create --step and plan show --fields id,title,steps, get/list/context/search/contracts, history --verify, validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift, health --check-only --summary, close --validate-close warn, and release. Summary: task pm-mteo, list_count=1, context_active=2, plan_steps=1, validate_ok=true, health_ok=true."
  "2026-05-23T10:55:23.564Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Implementation follow-up 2026-05-23: applied profiler feedback for bootstrap flag parity. src/cli.ts now keeps --no-extensions --version and --version --no-extensions on the fast package-json version path instead of importing cli/main. Local probe after build: --version 31-37ms, --no-extensions --version 32-37ms, --version --no-extensions 33-39ms. Added release-readiness coverage for --no-extensions --version."
  "2026-05-23T11:00:44.800Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Final local gate evidence 2026-05-23: direct full release gate passed after compile-cache startup optimization and --no-extensions version fast-path parity. Command: node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json. Results: build ok, typecheck ok, docs-skills ok, static quality ok, coverage 100 files / 1487 tests / 100% statements branches functions lines, version policy 2026.5.23 ok, secret scan ok, npx packed-package smoke ok, package-first dogfood 84 workflows ok, npm pack dry-run ok, compatibility check ok from base 2026.5.18, Sentry/telemetry required gate ok with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=3, failures_without_error_code_rows=0. Earlier linked pm test run had one transient npx-smoke calendar failure; the same packed smoke passed on direct rerun before this final gate."
  "2026-05-23T11:01:57.947Z",codex-extensive-agent,"PR evidence 2026-05-23: pushed commit da55067f on branch codex/startup-compile-cache-fast-version and opened PR #48 Improve CLI startup with compile cache at https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/pull/48. Beginning required >=15 minute AI-review wait and GitHub check watch before merge."
  "2026-05-23T11:13:31.208Z",codex-extensive-agent,"AI review response 2026-05-23: addressed valid PR #48 feedback. CodeRabbit requested explicit reverse-order --version coverage, so release-readiness now tests both --no-extensions --version and --version --no-extensions. Gemini noted shared temp cache permission risk, so the default Node compile-cache directory now includes a per-user key while preserving PM_CLI_COMPILE_CACHE_DIR override. CodeRabbit .agents/pm direct-edit comments were verified as false positives because all tracker mutations in this branch were produced through pm commands. Focused verification passed: pnpm build; fast-version probe for all three forms; PM_RUN_TESTS_SKIP_BUILD=1 node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts --reporter=dot; node scripts/check-secrets.mjs; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json."
  "2026-05-23T11:17:38.842Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Post-review final gate 2026-05-23: after applying CodeRabbit reverse-order version test and Gemini per-user compile-cache directory hardening, reran node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json. Passed: build, typecheck, docs-skills, static quality, coverage 100 files / 1487 tests / 100%, version policy 2026.5.23, secret scan, npx packed-package smoke, package-first dogfood 84 workflows, npm pack dry-run, compatibility check from base 2026.5.18, and required Sentry/telemetry gate with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.98, failures_without_error_code_rows=0."
  "2026-05-23T11:25:19.424Z",codex-extensive-agent,"Merge evidence 2026-05-23: PR #48 merged into main as merge commit fa065789 after refreshed head 3d61a23d had all GitHub checks green: build foundation, ubuntu Node 20, macOS Node 20, coverage, typecheck, static, compat, smokes, Sourcery, and CodeRabbit. Valid review feedback was applied before merge: reverse-order --version test coverage and per-user default compile-cache directory. Gemini cache-permission feedback addressed; CodeRabbit tracker direct-edit comments were false positives because pm commands produced .agents/pm mutations."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-17T09:12:12.755Z",codex-agent,"Benchmark method: spawned fresh node dist/cli.js processes per run from repo root, PM_AUTHOR=codex-agent, no PM_PATH overrides (real tracker), maxBuffer 20-30MiB. Collected both repeated timing arrays and one-shot --profile outputs with and without --no-extensions."
  "2026-05-22T15:45:00.043Z",maintainer-agent,"Partial progress 2026-05-22: removed zod from settings hot path (settings import 157ms->14ms; --help 227->140ms; list 540->340ms). The remaining startup levers are (a) esbuild bundling (this item) to collapse module-resolution overhead, and (b) item-store full-scan cost for list/context/search (context still ~556ms reading ~786 item files; no read cache - index/ dir is empty). esbuild bundle would mainly help the per-module resolution; an item-store read index would help the scan-bound commands."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-17T09:27:52.419Z",codex-agent,"Durable learning: startup refactors that replace static imports with dynamic imports can trigger orphan-module governance checks; preserving type-only import edges keeps static-quality graph integrity while maintaining runtime lazy-loading."
